The paper discusses the use of machine learning for malware analysis, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also extensively discusses different machine learning techniques and their application in malware analysis, which makes it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the practical implementation of these techniques, which makes it relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves data analysis and classification, which makes it relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
